You are working on a production-level web application.

This project already has an established design system.
Your primary responsibility is to PRESERVE and RESPECT this design system.

Do NOT redesign anything.
Do NOT introduce new styles unless explicitly requested.

==================================================
CORE DESIGN PRINCIPLE
==================================================

Consistency over creativity.

Every UI change must feel like it already belongs to the product.

==================================================
COLOR SYSTEM RULES
==================================================

- NEVER introduce new colors.
- ONLY use existing color tokens (primary, secondary, neutral, border, muted, background).

- Do NOT:
  - randomly use Tailwind colors (like blue-500, red-600, etc.)
  - add gradients unless already used
  - use brand colors (Facebook blue, YouTube red, etc.)

- All UI elements must follow the existing color hierarchy:
  - Primary = CTA (e.g. "Hızlı Başvur")
  - Neutral = background, cards
  - Muted = secondary text, labels
  - Border = subtle separation

==================================================
TYPOGRAPHY RULES
==================================================

- Do NOT introduce new fonts.
- Use ONLY the existing font family.

- Maintain typography scale:
  - Title
  - Subtitle
  - Body
  - Caption

- Do NOT:
  - randomly change font sizes
  - mix inconsistent font weights
  - create visual imbalance

==================================================
SPACING & LAYOUT RULES
==================================================

- Follow existing spacing system (padding, margin, gap)
- Keep alignment consistent

- Do NOT:
  - compress UI too much
  - create crowded layouts
  - introduce inconsistent spacing

- All components must feel:
  - breathable
  - balanced
  - aligned

==================================================
COMPONENT CONSISTENCY
==================================================

- Reuse existing components whenever possible:
  - buttons
  - chips
  - badges
  - cards
  - modals

- Do NOT create new component styles unless absolutely necessary

- If a new component is required:
  - it must visually match existing components
  - same border radius
  - same shadow system
  - same interaction style

==================================================
BUTTON RULES
==================================================

- Primary button style must remain dominant
- Secondary buttons must stay visually lighter

- Do NOT:
  - create new button colors
  - mix button styles randomly
  - break CTA hierarchy

==================================================
ICON RULES
==================================================

- Icons must be:
  - consistent style
  - same stroke / size

- Do NOT:
  - use colored icons (unless system already uses)
  - mix icon libraries

==================================================
VISUAL HIERARCHY
==================================================

- Important elements must stand out:
  - CTA buttons
  - Titles
  - Scores (Kurumsallık Skoru)

- Secondary elements must stay subtle:
  - labels
  - tags
  - metadata

==================================================
MOBILE / RESPONSIVE RULES
==================================================

- UI must remain clean on:
  - mobile
  - tablet
  - desktop

- Do NOT:
  - stack elements poorly
  - create overflow issues
  - break readability

==================================================
WHAT YOU MUST ALWAYS DO
==================================================

Before implementing any UI change, ask:

1) Does this match existing design language?
2) Does this introduce inconsistency?
3) Would a user notice this as “different”?

If YES → DO NOT IMPLEMENT

==================================================
WHAT YOU MUST NEVER DO
==================================================

- Do NOT redesign components
- Do NOT experiment visually
- Do NOT add “cool” but inconsistent UI
- Do NOT break design consistency

==================================================
FINAL GOAL
==================================================

Every new UI element must feel like:
“It was always part of this product.”

Not:
“This was added later.”
